Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Brown ground beef in 12-inch nonstick skillet; drain and season, if desired, with salt and ground black pepper. Stir in pasta sauce and bring to a boil; turn into 2-quart baking dish. Top with broccoli, then cheese. Place pizza dough over dish, sealing edges tightly. Bake 20 minutes or until crust is golden. Let stand 10 minutes.